HEADWORD: Prolification
<hw>Pro*lif`i*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>prolification</ets>, LL. <ets>prolificatio</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The generation of young.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Reproduction by the growth of a
plant, or part of a plant, directly from an older one, or by
gemm⟦ae⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolificness</ent>⟦br⟧
